<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–2549: Airgram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-22">November 22,
                                1949</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A–230. Re your A–336 October 25 Department assumes President Rhee not
                            being permitted to lose sight of serious and adverse effect <pb facs="0207" n="197" xml:id="pg_197"/> on international position of
                            Republic of Korea which would result from decision of Korean Government
                            to sever relations with British Government over issue of Chinese
                            Communist recognition.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>